The paper discusses the use of bibliometric novelty indicators to measure the novelty of papers, which is a topic related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social networks (cs.SI). The study also involves analyzing tags assigned to papers, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
